# gen142 (E3): pragmatic intent from turn SHAPE, not from a phrase list.
# mod_chitchat/mod_social already cover the affective register, but with growing
# cue lists — a held-out phrasing of the same speech act still hit the wall. This
# module infers the SPEECH ACT from structural FEATURES (opener class, a content
# predicate, negation, contrastive connective, a stance predicate, a hedge, an
# open-quantifier object, a topic-intro frame) and routes each act to a DIFFERENT
# move, so unseen phrasings transfer. It runs late (after every content module),
# and a leading discourse marker wrapping content is peeled BEFORE dispatch.

# --- soft request (open quantifier, no concrete object) -> invite a thread.
> give me something to think about
< Happy to. Pick a thread — your day, a small fact to remember, or something to reason about — and I'll run with it.

# --- hesitation (hedge markers, nothing concrete) -> lower the stakes.
> hmm i guess maybe
< No pressure — we can take it slowly. What's on your mind?

# --- disagreement (NEGATED stance predicate) -> accept pushback, invite the fix.
> i do not really agree with you
< Fair enough — tell me where I went wrong, and we can take it from there.

# --- topic-change invitation (modal opener + frame + object) -> steer onto X,
#     the object pulled by SHAPE (head noun after the frame), not memorized.
> could we chat about cheese
< Sure, let's talk about cheese. What about cheese is on your mind?

# --- mixed social + content: a discourse-marker opener wraps a real question.
#     The opener is peeled and the residue re-dispatched, so the CONTENT survives.
> socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> anyway, is socrates a man
< Yes.

# --- the same peel preserves an arithmetic task wrapped in a chatty opener
#     (the extra opener tokens used to shift a content parser onto the wrong word).
> by the way what is 2 plus 2
< 4.

# --- anti-impostor: a real (unfulfillable) request names a CONCRETE object, so it
#     is NOT a fill-the-silence soft request — it gets the honest wall, not a move.
> tell me a story about dragons
< I don't understand that yet.

# --- anti-impostor: a genuine knowledge question carries no pragmatic shape and
#     no content the KB knows, so pragma declines and the honest wall stands (the
#     prior turn was already the classic wall, so the non-repeating fallback varies).
> is the sky blue?
< I didn't quite catch that. What would you like to know?
